mri:abstract.gco:CharacterString: These ESRI shape files are of National Park Service tract and boundary data that was created by the Land Resources Division. Tracts are numbered and created by the regional cartographic staff at the Land Resources Program Centers and are associated to the Land Status Maps. This data should be used to display properties that NPS owns and properties that NPS may have some type of interest such as scenic easements or right of ways.

mri:purpose.gco:CharacterString: This data is intended to keep a record of ownership information. Tracts can represent several types of interest like fee and scenic easement, and can be under several types of ownership like NPS owned, private, other federal, state or county. This data set provides accurate and reliable ownership data for park management and acquisition priorities.

mco:useLimitation.gco:CharacterString: NPS Director's Order #25 states: "Land status maps will be prepared to identify the ownership of the lands within the authorized boundaries of the park unit. These maps, showing ownership and acreage, are the 'official record' of the acreage of Federal and non-federal lands within the park boundaries. While these maps are the official record of the lands and acreage within the unit's authorized boundaries, they are not of survey quality and not intended to be used for survey purposes." As such this data is intended for use as a tool for GIS analysis. It is in no way intended for engineering or legal purposes. The data accuracy is checked against best available sources which may be dated and vary by location. NPS assumes no liability for use of this data. The boundary polygons LRD creates represent the current legislated boundary of a given NPS unit. NPS does not necessarily have full fee ownership or hold another interest (easement, right of way, etc...) in all parcels contained within this boundary. Equivalently NPS may own or have an interest in parcels outside the legislated boundary of a given unit. In order to obtain complete information about current NPS interests both inside and outside the units legislated boundary, the tracts file created by LRD should be used in conjunction with this boundary file created by LRD.

mdq:measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: Link and node polygon topology is created using AutoCAD Civil 3D 2012. The data is then exported to ESRI shape file format and reprojected from it's native Autodesk coordinate system to NAD83 generic latitude and longitude, LL83.

Information contained in LRD's land ownership databases is updated nightly however tract polygons are posted to the NPS Data Store on a monthly basis. Users can ensure parcel polygons have up to date ownership attribution after the publication date by contacting your regional LRD office or downloading the Current_Tract_Ownership_Data file located on the NPS Data Store (http://science.nature.nps.gov/nrdata/) in a dBase format. Please contact the data originator with any suggested corrections and updates. LRD's boundary polygons represent the current legislated boundary of a given NPS unit. NPS does not necessarily have full fee ownership or hold another interest (easement, right of way, etc...) in all parcels contained within this boundary. Equivalently NPS may own or have an interest in parcels outside the legislated boundary of a given unit. In order to obtain complete information about current NPS interests both inside and outside the units legislated boundary, LRD's tracts files should also be downloaded and used in conjunction with LRD's boundary files.

mrl:description.gco:CharacterString: Per Federal Register/Vol. 81 11/Tuesday, January 19, 2016/Notices, the park boundary of Yosemite National Park is modified to 400 acres of land known as Ackerson Meadow and identified as NPS Tract 20-133, in Tuolunne County. Using the CadNSDI PLSS is how Tract 20-133 was drawn in in dwg file. Legal description of said tract is described in aliquot parts located in Sections 23 and 24, T. 1 S., R. 19 E., M.D. B. & M. Therefore, the tract and boundary topology of each layer was updated. By Federal Register Notices Volume, No. 142 dated July 24, 2013, Tract 20-132 is now included within Yosemite National Park boundary. On November 13, 2012 a new topologies were generated to include the latest tract (Tract 20-132) added to MIS system and currently outside to park boundary. This tract is in process to be included the park boundary by Federal Register Notices. The legal description of said tract is in aliquot parts (The N1/2 of the NE ¼ of Section 35, T. 3 S., R. 20 E., M. D. B and M.) 80.00 acre parcel. Using PLSS layer of the original dwg file prepared by contractor Avineon that’s how Tract 20-132 was drawn in dwg file. Avenion preparation__ Data was digitize from Yosemite National Park Land Status Map using AutoCad in CA State Plane, NAD83, feet. NAD83 California State Planes, Zone III, US Foot was used as the source coordinate system for the AutoCAD Civil 3D 2012 project. The Autodesk line work is imported, edited, attributed, approved, and a link and node topology is developed both for the tract and boundary data layers according to the procedures described in the Land Acquisition Procedures Manual Chapter 5. The entire unit is created in a geographically contiguous model space and separate layouts representing each individual segment map are created. The tract and boundary data is then reprojected to North American Datum 1983 generic latitude & longitude and exported from Autodesk to an ArcView shape file format in a single step.

mrl:description.gco:CharacterString: ***Made several spatial and attribute adjustments to tract and boundary datasets. Fixed boundary based on best available data sources - data provided by Yosemite NP GIS Specialist, enabling legislation, PLSS division lines, USGS NHD data, USFS administrative boundary. Adjusted tract geometries for those tracts that share segments with park boundary to maintain consistency between tract and boundary feature classes. Restructured El Portal Admin site area tracts based on data provided by regional lands cartographer.***
